raw_data.description: Works independently or under limited supervision, manages and coordinates with internal or external parties the collection, compilation, normalization, and standard analysis of data assets across diverse projects and data platforms. Decides on hardware and software design needs and acts according to the decisions. Serves as a data subject matter expert, collaborates with business owners or external clients to establish an analysis plan to answer key business questions, and delivers both reporting results and insights. Generates specific and operational reports in support of objectives and initiatives, and presents and communicates complex analytical data and results to appropriate audiences.  Routinely supervises or mentors more junior employees.

raw_data.description: Works independently or under limited supervision, expertly monitors computer networks for security issues. Investigates security breaches and other cybersecurity incidents. Documents security breaches and assesses the damage they cause. Directly works with the security team to perform tests and uncover network vulnerabilities, such as penetration testing. Leads and fixes detected vulnerabilities to maintain a high-security standard. Evaluates and recommends best practices for IT security. Expertly installs security measures and operating software to protect systems and information infrastructure, including firewalls and data encryption programs. Conducts in- depth analysis, confirming intrusion information and creating a forensically sound duplicate of the files. Decrypts data and provides technical summaries and input. Examines recovered data for relevant information and performs dynamic analysis to include timeline, statistical, and file signature analysis. Performs real-time cyber defense handling tasks to support deployable Incident Response Teams (IRTs). Routinely supervises or mentors more junior employees.

raw_data.title: Information System Security Officer (ISSO) - Senior
raw_data.description: Works independently or under limited supervision, manages the information security management function of an organization, including the development, documentation, implementation, operation, and maintenance of an information security program; and conducts ongoing activities to preserve the availability, integrity, and confidentiality of organization information resources in compliance with applicable security policies and standards. Maintains security protocols; and safeguards the organization's computers, networks, and data against threats, such as security breaches, computer viruses, or attacks by cyber- criminals, avoiding loss of confidential information, and fines from regulatory agencies for failing to protect data. Communicates regularly with other managers, and brings the organization's information security risks under explicit management control. May establish, update, and oversee the cybersecurity program of an information system or network. May manage COMSEC resources (CNSSI 4009) or key custodian for a crypto key management system (CKMS). May perform or assist with reviewing, developing, and navigating the system, team, and customer through the Authority to Operate (ATO) accreditation/ certification documentation process. May perform network self-inspections. May create new and.or edit existing documentation that forms the ATO package to include the System Security Plan and IS contingency plan. May develop Plan of Action and Milestone (POAMS) from vulnerability data and enter into the system of record. May routinely supervises or mentors more junior employees.
